Yes — that’s a bug/regression in that revision.

`borderStylesReset` emits `border-width: 0`, and `@apply border-dotted` copies both matching `.border-dotted` rules into the target:

```css
border-width: 0;
border-style: dotted;
```

So the style is valid, but there is no visible border. The reset also makes utility composition order-dependent.

As a workaround, set the width after applying the style:

```css
.foo {
  @apply border-dotted;
  border-width: 1px;
}
```

Your reading of the two linked sections is correct; the reset should not be attached to the same `border-dotted`/`border-dashed` utilities in a way that `@apply` inherits it.
